translate ru strings:

    old "All alone in one of the greatest cities on earth."
    new "All alone in one of the greatest cities on earth."

    old "Sarah would forever wonder at how odd it was that she felt most alone in the largest of crowds."
    new "Sarah would forever wonder at how odd it was that she felt most alone in the largest of crowds."

    old "Something about other people reminded her of how she had no people left in her life."
    new "Something about other people reminded her of how she had no people left in her life."

    old "Her father, her brother. Everyone she had ever met in Castle Reinmeer, all dead or worse by now."
    new "Her father, her brother. Everyone she had ever met in Castle Reinmeer, all dead or worse by now."

    old "And here she was, away from it all..."
    new "And here she was, away from it all..."

    old "Not to mention, the voice that had called out to her..."
    new "Not to mention, the voice that had called out to her..."

    old "What did it mean?"
    new "What did it mean?"

    old "It had said that it waited by a dark fountain, but Sarah was a stranger to the city."
    new "It had said that it waited by a dark fountain, but Sarah was a stranger to the city."

    old "Did it even have a fountain?"
    new "Did it even have a fountain?"

    old "She had wanted a new life, and against all odds, had gotten a chance at it. She had to forget the past. Learn to let it go."
    new "She had wanted a new life, and against all odds, had gotten a chance at it. She had to forget the past. Learn to let it go."

    old "She focussed her mind."
    new "She focussed her mind."

    old "For now, there were more pressing issues, more immediate."
    new "For now, there were more pressing issues, more immediate."

    old "Food. Housing."
    new "Food. Housing."

    old "Given her current condition, she had little time to speculate on peculiar voices."
    new "Given her current condition, she had little time to speculate on peculiar voices."

    old "Sarah kept following the road. With each step, she crowds seem to grow larger."
    new "Sarah kept following the road. With each step, she crowds seem to grow larger."

    old "Before long, Sarah came upon a square."
    new "Before long, Sarah came upon a square."

    old "All over, crowds of people hustled and bustled in various directions."
    new "All over, crowds of people hustled and bustled in various directions."

    old "Shops near the edges of the square were alive with commerce, people rushing in and out, carts full of goods flowing from one end to the other."
    new "Shops near the edges of the square were alive with commerce, people rushing in and out, carts full of goods flowing from one end to the other."

    old "The more Sarah looked at it, the more it felt to her like the ant colonies she'd go look for in the summer with Thomas."
    new "The more Sarah looked at it, the more it felt to her like the ant colonies she'd go look for in the summer with Thomas."

    old "A vast, mesmerizing swarm of people. Each moving about for their own particular ends, but all together, one sprawling industrious hive."
    new "A vast, mesmerizing swarm of people. Each moving about for their own particular ends, but all together, one sprawling industrious hive."

    old "Sarah felt overwhelmed."
    new "Sarah felt overwhelmed."

    old "In the capital of Rosanna, there were plenty of people, but it all looked provincial compared to this."
    new "In the capital of Rosanna, there were plenty of people, but it all looked provincial compared to this."

    old "She had never fully realized just how trivial her homeland had been in the grand design of the world."
    new "She had never fully realized just how trivial her homeland had been in the grand design of the world."

    old "Looking up ahead, Sarah saw the road break apart into many more directions. Each equally busy."
    new "Looking up ahead, Sarah saw the road break apart into many more directions. Each equally busy."

    old "Sarah understood that this square, one of the busiest she'd ever seen in her life, might just be one of many in this city."
    new "Sarah understood that this square, one of the busiest she'd ever seen in her life, might just be one of many in this city."

    old "This city that went on forever."
    new "This city that went on forever."

    old "Turning her head up, she saw the black side of the massive pyramid."
    new "Turning her head up, she saw the black side of the massive pyramid."

    old "It was strange how the enormous thing seemed to exist in the background of the city."
    new "It was strange how the enormous thing seemed to exist in the background of the city."

    old "Nobody seemed to pay it much mind."
    new "Nobody seemed to pay it much mind."

    old "Even Sarah realized that in such a short time in Rahayal, she'd found it hard to really acknowledge the object."
    new "Even Sarah realized that in such a short time in Rahayal, she'd found it hard to really acknowledge the object."

    old "It was the size of the thing, she concluded."
    new "It was the size of the thing, she concluded."

    old "The black pyramid loomed so large over the city, that it was impossible to even really look at the entire thing."
    new "The black pyramid loomed so large over the city, that it was impossible to even really look at the entire thing."

    old "Anywhere she looked, she could only really look at parts of it, making the whole of the pyramid somehow hard to grasp."
    new "Anywhere she looked, she could only really look at parts of it, making the whole of the pyramid somehow hard to grasp."

    old "Focus, she told herself."
    new "Focus, she told herself."

    old "This was a new city. A new chance. She needed to make the most of it if she wanted to avoid sleeping on the streets like in Lethram."
    new "This was a new city. A new chance. She needed to make the most of it if she wanted to avoid sleeping on the streets like in Lethram."

    old "Sarah could feel the weight of the money in her pocket."
    new "Sarah could feel the weight of the money in her pocket."

    old "A decent sum. She wouldn't live off it forever, but it would keep her housed for a good while. Enough to make a plan."
    new "A decent sum. She wouldn't live off it forever, but it would keep her housed for a good while. Enough to make a plan."

    old "A sign caught her attention from the corner of her eyes."
    new "A sign caught her attention from the corner of her eyes."

    old "Dunstin Family Inn."
    new "Dunstin Family Inn."

    old "She would need to spend the night somewhere, and she found the word family somehow appealing."
    new "She would need to spend the night somewhere, and she found the word family somehow appealing."

    old "Sarah headed to the inn and stepped inside."
    new "Sarah headed to the inn and stepped inside."

    old "The moment she stepped inside, she found the atmosphere to her liking."
    new "The moment she stepped inside, she found the atmosphere to her liking."

    old "There were a few patrons about, but nothing too busy. The sounds of the city were still here, but muted."
    new "There were a few patrons about, but nothing too busy. The sounds of the city were still here, but muted."

    old "She liked the calm of the place."
    new "She liked the calm of the place."

    old "Off in the distance, a hearth was lit with a low fire. A pot stewing on top of it."
    new "Off in the distance, a hearth was lit with a low fire. A pot stewing on top of it."

    old "Sarah sat down at a table in the corner."
    new "Sarah sat down at a table in the corner."

    old "With her back to the wall, looking out over the easy and happy faces of the other patrons, she was struck by an odd feeling."
    new "With her back to the wall, looking out over the easy and happy faces of the other patrons, she was struck by an odd feeling."

    old "It was like a pain, long suffered, nwo suddenly gone. Like an unending noise, suddenly quieted."
    new "It was like a pain, long suffered, nwo suddenly gone. Like an unending noise, suddenly quieted."

    old "Sarah realized that in this brief moment, she felt calm."
    new "Sarah realized that in this brief moment, she felt calm."

    old "She felt calm as she not felt in weeks. Months now."
    new "She felt calm as she not felt in weeks. Months now."

    old "A peace she hadn't felt since the tragedy of her country. The death of her brother."
    new "A peace she hadn't felt since the tragedy of her country. The death of her brother."

    old "Guilt rushed in to her heart nearly as quickly."
    new "Guilt rushed in to her heart nearly as quickly."

    old "How could she sit here and feel at peace, when all she had ever loved were ruined?"
    new "How could she sit here and feel at peace, when all she had ever loved were ruined?"

    old "And still, the fire in the hearth crackled. The faces on the patrons, happy. The feeling in the air, light and easy."
    new "And still, the fire in the hearth crackled. The faces on the patrons, happy. The feeling in the air, light and easy."

    old "The pain that she felt was dulled."
    new "The pain that she felt was dulled."

    old "It was still there, but it had begun to lessen. To transform into something else, or perhaps begin a process of transformation."
    new "It was still there, but it had begun to lessen. To transform into something else, or perhaps begin a process of transformation."

    old "Whichever it was, Sarah could not be certain, only that the feelings of pain were different now than they had been before."
    new "Whichever it was, Sarah could not be certain, only that the feelings of pain were different now than they had been before."

    old "Change."
    new "Change."

    old "That alone gave her cause to wonder."
    new "That alone gave her cause to wonder."

    old "Not that she might one day forget her brother, for she knew she would remember Thomas for as long as she lived."
    new "Not that she might one day forget her brother, for she knew she would remember Thomas for as long as she lived."

    old "But instead that perhaps, the pain of her loss, though deep, would not prove fatal."
    new "But instead that perhaps, the pain of her loss, though deep, would not prove fatal."

    old "That instead, she might yet live anew."
    new "That instead, she might yet live anew."

    old "In this place. This strange and foreign city that had so long sat at the center of all the world."
    new "In this place. This strange and foreign city that had so long sat at the center of all the world."

    old "Innkeeper\" \"Good mornin there."
    new "Innkeeper\" \"Good mornin there."

    old "Sarah looked up, suddenly startled from her thoughts."
    new "Sarah looked up, suddenly startled from her thoughts."

    old "Ooh, hello. I...I'm sorry, am I taking up a spot?"
    new "Ooh, hello. I...I'm sorry, am I taking up a spot?"

    old "The man smiled a wide and genuine smile."
    new "The man smiled a wide and genuine smile."

    old "Innkeeper\" \"Nah, not if you're a payin customer that is."
    new "Innkeeper\" \"Nah, not if you're a payin customer that is."

    old "He laughed, his voice booming, the kind of laugh of a man who didn't seem to ever pretend being anything other than what he was."
    new "He laughed, his voice booming, the kind of laugh of a man who didn't seem to ever pretend being anything other than what he was."

    old "Innkeeper\" \"I only joke."
    new "Innkeeper\" \"I only joke."

    old "Innkeeper\" \"You want to sit here all day, that's fine by me, but I imagine you might be hungry."
    new "Innkeeper\" \"You want to sit here all day, that's fine by me, but I imagine you might be hungry."

    old "Sarah breathed in the air."
    new "Sarah breathed in the air."

    old "For the first time, she consciously smelled the spiced aroma that rose up from the stew on the fire."
    new "For the first time, she consciously smelled the spiced aroma that rose up from the stew on the fire."

    old "If she had not been hungry, the smell alone would have made her so."
    new "If she had not been hungry, the smell alone would have made her so."

    old "That's...what is that smell?"
    new "That's...what is that smell?"

    old "Innkeeper\" \"Ooh that? That's our Inn's famous Dunstin Stew."
    new "Innkeeper\" \"Ooh that? That's our Inn's famous Dunstin Stew."

    old "Dunstin?"
    new "Dunstin?"

    old "Innkeeper\" \"This here is the Dunstin Inn. We got Dunstin Stew. And as you might suspect, I'm Ramsey Dunstin."
    new "Innkeeper\" \"This here is the Dunstin Inn. We got Dunstin Stew. And as you might suspect, I'm Ramsey Dunstin."

    old "Ramsey...Dunstin."
    new "Ramsey...Dunstin."

    old "That's right. Proud owner of this fine establishment."
    new "That's right. Proud owner of this fine establishment."

    old "Got it from my parents, who got it from theirs. They say the Inn has been in our family for more than two centuries"
    new "Got it from my parents, who got it from theirs. They say the Inn has been in our family for more than two centuries"

    old "He laughed, loudly."
    new "He laughed, loudly."

    old "Sarah was impressed. She had only ever known kings and emperors who could trace their lines back like that."
    new "Sarah was impressed. She had only ever known kings and emperors who could trace their lines back like that."

    old "Keeping an Inn up for such a time was no small feat."
    new "Keeping an Inn up for such a time was no small feat."

    old "That's very impressive."
    new "That's very impressive."

    old "Thank you kindly for the compliment, but I'll have to share some of that credit."
    new "Thank you kindly for the compliment, but I'll have to share some of that credit."

    old "Share it?"
    new "Share it?"

    old "This here is a family business, and I couldn't run it without my family."
    new "This here is a family business, and I couldn't run it without my family."

    old "He gestured towards two young people, one carrying a barrel on his shoulders, the other a girl taking orders from a different table."
    new "He gestured towards two young people, one carrying a barrel on his shoulders, the other a girl taking orders from a different table."

    old "Each seemed about her age."
    new "Each seemed about her age."

    old "Thems my kids, Jacob and Elsa. Dunstin of course, gotta carry the family name."
    new "Thems my kids, Jacob and Elsa. Dunstin of course, gotta carry the family name."

    old "Ramsey seemed to beam as he talked of his children."
    new "Ramsey seemed to beam as he talked of his children."

    old "You have a beautiful family."
    new "You have a beautiful family."

    old "Thank you kindly."
    new "Thank you kindly."

    old "But what about yourself? Not to be too intrusive, I know some guests like to keep to themselves, but we don't get a lot like you."
    new "But what about yourself? Not to be too intrusive, I know some guests like to keep to themselves, but we don't get a lot like you."

    old "Like me?"
    new "Like me?"

    old "Pretty ladies travelling all by themselves."
    new "Pretty ladies travelling all by themselves."

    old "Sarah blushed at his sudden compliment."
    new "Sarah blushed at his sudden compliment."

    old "I just arrived in the city...I hope it's not an issue."
    new "I just arrived in the city...I hope it's not an issue."

    old "An issue? By the Gods no, that ain't how I meant it."
    new "An issue? By the Gods no, that ain't how I meant it."

    old "Rahayal is just about the safest place in all the world. Even a lady by herself ain't got nothin to worry about."
    new "Rahayal is just about the safest place in all the world. Even a lady by herself ain't got nothin to worry about."

    old "It's just rare is all I'm sayin."
    new "It's just rare is all I'm sayin."

    old "But if I'm askin too many questions, just tell me to get lost. I sometimes forget myself and ramble on."
    new "But if I'm askin too many questions, just tell me to get lost. I sometimes forget myself and ramble on."

    old "The truth was, she was somewhat happy to actually meet a friendly person for once."
    new "The truth was, she was somewhat happy to actually meet a friendly person for once."

    old "I came in from Lethram, and I'm goin about seeing to finding some work."
    new "I came in from Lethram, and I'm goin about seeing to finding some work."

    old "Before that, I thought I might find a place to stay, so I came to this Inn."
    new "Before that, I thought I might find a place to stay, so I came to this Inn."

    old "Ramsey loudly laughed again."
    new "Ramsey loudly laughed again."

    old "Well Gods, ain't no better Inn than the Dunstin Inn."
    new "Well Gods, ain't no better Inn than the Dunstin Inn."

    old "A fair price and we treat all our customers like family, not like those big places that just want your money."
    new "A fair price and we treat all our customers like family, not like those big places that just want your money."

    old "Ooh, so you have rooms to spare?"
    new "Ooh, so you have rooms to spare?"

    old "Ramsey nodded."
    new "Ramsey nodded."

    old "That we do. A few open actually, there is a nice one that has a view of the plaza outside."
    new "That we do. A few open actually, there is a nice one that has a view of the plaza outside."

    old "And...the rate?"
    new "And...the rate?"

    old "Sarah felt her muscles tense. How far would her money really take her in this city?"
    new "Sarah felt her muscles tense. How far would her money really take her in this city?"

    old "Ramsey shrugged."
    new "Ramsey shrugged."

    old "Usual rate is about ten Mythrani to a night, but I can make you a discount."
    new "Usual rate is about ten Mythrani to a night, but I can make you a discount."

    old "A discount, really? Why?"
    new "A discount, really? Why?"

    old "He quickly winked at her."
    new "He quickly winked at her."

    old "Keepin a pretty lady around is good for business."
    new "Keepin a pretty lady around is good for business."

    old "Sarah felt herself blush again. Though the man was far from ideal, he liked to play the charmer."
    new "Sarah felt herself blush again. Though the man was far from ideal, he liked to play the charmer."

    old "This was still somewhat new to Sarah. Back in Rosanna, flirting with a member of the Royal family was not permitted."
    new "This was still somewhat new to Sarah. Back in Rosanna, flirting with a member of the Royal family was not permitted."

    old "Men at court kept to their wandering eyes only."
    new "Men at court kept to their wandering eyes only."

    old "Here, in the world, where she was no longer a princess, people treated her differently."
    new "Here, in the world, where she was no longer a princess, people treated her differently."

    old "In some ways, it was hard to get used to, in others she quite enjoyed it."
    new "In some ways, it was hard to get used to, in others she quite enjoyed it."

    old "Enjoyed being treated as a human being, an equal, rather than some nobility far beyond reproach."
    new "Enjoyed being treated as a human being, an equal, rather than some nobility far beyond reproach."

    old "Well, where I come from, turning down hospitality is considered poor manners, so I will take your discount."
    new "Well, where I come from, turning down hospitality is considered poor manners, so I will take your discount."

    old "Ramsey laughed."
    new "Ramsey laughed."

    old "Excellent, I'll get my boy Jacob to fix you up a room. The one with the view."
    new "Excellent, I'll get my boy Jacob to fix you up a room. The one with the view."

    old "Sarah smiled and gave a quick bow."
    new "Sarah smiled and gave a quick bow."

    old "Ooh, and one more thing."
    new "Ooh, and one more thing."

    old "Ramsey raised one eyebrow."
    new "Ramsey raised one eyebrow."

    old "Might I ask for a bowl of that stew?"
    new "Might I ask for a bowl of that stew?"

    old "Ramsey laughed loudly."
    new "Ramsey laughed loudly."

    old "Of course, first one is one the house."
    new "Of course, first one is one the house."

    old "You're too kind."
    new "You're too kind."

    old "That ain't no kindness little lady."
    new "That ain't no kindness little lady."

    old "Anybody that takes a bit from that stew is hooked."
    new "Anybody that takes a bit from that stew is hooked."

    old "Sarah watched as Ramsey walked away."
    new "Sarah watched as Ramsey walked away."

    old "He returned a moment later, giving her a bowl of the stew, still steaming."
    new "He returned a moment later, giving her a bowl of the stew, still steaming."

    old "Before she could say much, he was off to the next table."
    new "Before she could say much, he was off to the next table."

    old "She quickly saw that running and Inn was busy work indeed, as the whole of the Dunstin family rushed about."
    new "She quickly saw that running and Inn was busy work indeed, as the whole of the Dunstin family rushed about."

    old "Sitting in her corner, Sarah began to ate the stew."
    new "Sitting in her corner, Sarah began to ate the stew."

    old "Perhaps it was her deep hunger, or perhaps there was something about this moment, but Sarah had rarely ever tasted anything quite this good."
    new "Perhaps it was her deep hunger, or perhaps there was something about this moment, but Sarah had rarely ever tasted anything quite this good."

    old "When Ramsey had passed her table for a brief moment, she had dared to ask."
    new "When Ramsey had passed her table for a brief moment, she had dared to ask."

    old "What's in it?"
    new "What's in it?"

    old "Ramsey had only given her a mischievous smile."
    new "Ramsey had only given her a mischievous smile."

    old "Old family secret, I'm afraid."
    new "Old family secret, I'm afraid."

    old "When she had finished eating her food and was ever more content, Sarah finally asked about the room."
    new "When she had finished eating her food and was ever more content, Sarah finally asked about the room."

    old "As promised, it was Ramsey's son Jacob who took her to the room."
    new "As promised, it was Ramsey's son Jacob who took her to the room."

    old "Sarah followed Ramsey's son up the stairs."
    new "Sarah followed Ramsey's son up the stairs."

    old "The young man had offered to carry what little she had. Insisted was perhaps more accurate."
    new "The young man had offered to carry what little she had. Insisted was perhaps more accurate."

    old "She followed him up the stairs of the Inn, down the hallway, and into the room."
    new "She followed him up the stairs of the Inn, down the hallway, and into the room."

    old "Just as promised, it was a perfectly fine room was a view of the plaza that made the room appear more than it was."
    new "Just as promised, it was a perfectly fine room was a view of the plaza that made the room appear more than it was."

    old "There we go."
    new "There we go."

    old "He placed her few belongings down on the table."
    new "He placed her few belongings down on the table."

    old "This is the key to the room."
    new "This is the key to the room."

    old "He added it to the rest of Sarah's belongings."
    new "He added it to the rest of Sarah's belongings."

    old "Sarah first observed the room, but when she had taken all of it in, she instead looked at the young man before her."
    new "Sarah first observed the room, but when she had taken all of it in, she instead looked at the young man before her."

    old "For a brief moment, she couldn't quite understand what it was about Jacob that confused her."
    new "For a brief moment, she couldn't quite understand what it was about Jacob that confused her."

    old "Then she suddenly understood."
    new "Then she suddenly understood."

    old "Jacob, a young man who she guessed was quite close to her own age, was of a strong build with broad shoulders."
    new "Jacob, a young man who she guessed was quite close to her own age, was of a strong build with broad shoulders."

    old "A lifetime of working in his father's Inn had hardend his body in an appealing way."
    new "A lifetime of working in his father's Inn had hardend his body in an appealing way."

    old "Everything about him suggested to Sarah that he was one of those boys who went through life, smiling and confident."
    new "Everything about him suggested to Sarah that he was one of those boys who went through life, smiling and confident."

    old "Yet rather, he appeared to her the opposite."
    new "Yet rather, he appeared to her the opposite."

    old "He avoided meeting her eyes, instead staring more at the floor."
    new "He avoided meeting her eyes, instead staring more at the floor."

    old "And what little he said, was spoken briefly and quickly."
    new "And what little he said, was spoken briefly and quickly."

    old "If you have any questions, you can ask my dad, or me, or my sister Elsa."
    new "If you have any questions, you can ask my dad, or me, or my sister Elsa."

    old "It must be fun, running an Inn with your family."
    new "It must be fun, running an Inn with your family."

    old "Jacob only shrugged."
    new "Jacob only shrugged."

    old "I have to go back to work. Do you have any other questions?"
    new "I have to go back to work. Do you have any other questions?"

    old "With that, and without saying a word more, the odd boy dissapeared out of the room."
    new "With that, and without saying a word more, the odd boy dissapeared out of the room."

    old "As the door fell shut, Sarah smiled to herself. She began to take in the room all over again."
    new "As the door fell shut, Sarah smiled to herself. She began to take in the room all over again."

    old "Everything in her life had always been hers by birth."
    new "Everything in her life had always been hers by birth."

    old "This room...temporary as it was, had been one of the few things she'd achieved all on her own."
    new "This room...temporary as it was, had been one of the few things she'd achieved all on her own."

    old "Sarah fell onto the soft bed and closed her eyes."
    new "Sarah fell onto the soft bed and closed her eyes."

    old "Whatever might come in the future, she was safe and happy, if only for a moment."
    new "Whatever might come in the future, she was safe and happy, if only for a moment."

    old "Sarah didn't ask for more."
    new "Sarah didn't ask for more."

